[5.733, "o", "\r\n💡 \u001b[92mAnswer:\u001b[0m WOOHOO! Ah, what an EXCELLENT question!\r\n\r\nAccording to the provided context, specifically in the section comparing self-attention to recurrent layers, the three criteria evaluated regarding computational complexity, parallelizable computation, and path length are:\r\n\r\n1. **Total Computational Complexity per Layer**: This criterion compares the computational cost of each layer type.\r\n2. **Amount of Computation that can be Parallelized**: This evaluates how much computation can be done simultaneously, measured by the minimum number of sequential operations required.\r\n3. **Path Length between Long-Range Dependencies in the Network**: This examines how easily long-range dependencies can be learned within the network, with shorter paths making it easier to learn!\r\n\r\nAnd that's not all, folks! These criteria are crucial for evaluating the performance and efficiency of different layer types in sequence transduction tasks.\r\n\r\nSource: [The provided text], no specific chapter or section citation"]
